33:16.294 --> 33:22.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
living in a city
targeted by terrorists; and
celebrating 50

33:22.767 --> 33:25.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
years of music in a
world-renowned jazz club.

33:25.971 --> 33:32.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, we return to Latin
America, and
efforts to end the world's
longest-running

33:32.277 --> 33:34.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
conflict, in Colombia.

33:34.079 --> 33:39.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Havana today, Secretary of
State John Kerry
met with negotiators ahead of a
Wednesday

33:39.451 --> 33:45.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
deadline for Colombia's peace
talks. It included
a meeting with the main rebel
faction, the

33:45.457 --> 33:49.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia, or
FARC.

33:49.160 --> 33:55.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last month, I sat down with
Colombian President
Juan Manuel Santos to discuss
his peace initiative.

33:55.300 --> 34:01.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, the view from the rebel
side, in
Putumayo, deep in Colombia's
south.

34:01.439 --> 34:06.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondents Bruno
Federico and
Nadja Drost recently traveled
there for this

34:06.544 --> 34:12.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
exclusive report before the
Colombian government
banned reporters from events
like what you're

34:12.817 --> 34:13.952 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about to see.

34:13.985 --> 34:17.022 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The story is narrated by Ms.
Drost.

34:17.055 --> 34:24.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Beyond the end of
the road, the
Caqueta River winds deep into
Putumayo. There's

34:24.663 --> 34:28.099 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
endless jungle and the FARC.

34:28.133 --> 34:33.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After decades of cloaking their
movements
to evade the military, these
rebels are emerging

34:33.271 --> 34:39.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the jungle. It's for no
small reason:
In light of an expected peace
deal, the government

34:39.411 --> 34:44.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of President Juan Manuel Santos
has pulled
back its forces temporarily from
the area

34:44.716 --> 34:50.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to allow FARC commanders in
Havana to travel
here to talk peace directly with
their troops.

34:50.855 --> 34:55.226 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RAMIRO, FARC (through
translator): We had
the idea to do this out of a
necessity, so

34:55.260 --> 35:00.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that people, the guerrilla and
our communities,
can learn what is happening, so
that people

35:00.165 --> 35:02.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
have a hand in the peace
process.

35:02.267 --> 35:07.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NADJA DROST: Hundreds of
guerrillas gather
for a landmark event on the road
towards peace.

35:07.939 --> 35:12.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The FARC have also invited the
people they
have lived among for decades,
and us, the

35:12.610 --> 35:17.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
only foreign TV crew, to witness
the biggest
gathering of rebels and
civilians in over

35:17.615 --> 35:19.551 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a decade.

35:19.584 --> 35:23.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have been following units of
the FARC over
the last year, traveling to
their camps camouflaged

35:23.121 --> 35:28.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the jungle. Now it's the
first time seeing
them outside of their
clandestine life. After

35:28.426 --> 35:33.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
years of discreetly moving
through villages,
it's a rare and exceptional
sight to see dozens

35:33.565 --> 35:38.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of them walking in town
alongside civilians,
as everyone prepares for the
events.

35:38.703 --> 35:43.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): It's
important
because it might help clarify
doubts that

35:43.975 --> 35:45.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
many people have.

35:45.777 --> 35:54.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: It's no wonder
people have doubts;
50 years of conflict have killed
nearly a

35:54.652 --> 36:01.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
quarter-million people, and
displaced some
six million. Another 40,000 are
the disappeared.

36:01.259 --> 36:06.865 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Crimes have been committed by
all parties:
guerrilla groups, government
forces, and right-wing

36:06.898 --> 36:13.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
paramilitary groups who often
acted as a proxy
for the state. The FARC started
out in the

36:13.438 --> 36:19.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
1960s as small groups of armed
peasants defending
the rights of the poor. It
became a Marxist

36:19.244 --> 36:25.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
insurgency that later bolstered
its forces
using the drug trade,
kidnappings and extortion

36:25.183 --> 36:27.285 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to finance its their fight.

36:27.318 --> 36:32.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since 2000, the Colombian
military, backed
by billions of U.S. dollars, has
decimated

36:32.490 --> 36:37.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the FARC, and their ranks have
dropped to
an estimated 7,000 rebels today.
It was a

36:37.829 --> 36:41.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
weakened, but undefeated FARC
that came to
the negotiating table.

36:41.966 --> 36:47.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Joaquin Gomez, the nom de guerre
for the commander
of the FARC's powerful southern
bloc, got

36:47.205 --> 36:54.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
safe passage from Havana to
visit home. Alexandra
Narino, also an alias, has
returned with him.

36:54.579 --> 36:59.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A Dutch woman famous for being a
foreign rebel,
she's wanted in the U.S. for her
role in the

36:59.617 --> 37:06.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kidnapping of three American
military contractors
in 2003. They're big names here,
and across

37:06.591 --> 37:11.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Colombia, but rarely have they
shown their
faces in the territory they call
home.

37:11.863 --> 37:16.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People gather to ask the FARC if
what they
hear about the peace process is
true.

37:16.101 --> 37:21.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Will
there really
be a peace agreement signed by
March 23?

37:21.639 --> 37:27.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAQUIN GOMEZ, FARC (through
translator):
This is not possible. It's not
possible because

37:27.612 --> 37:31.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the government has to fulfill a
series of
commitments that, until now, it
hasn't.

37:31.783 --> 37:36.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Despite more than
three years
of negotiations, Gomez says
there are many

37:36.221 --> 37:40.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sticking points that have yet to
be resolved,
like how the FARC would disarm
and concentrate

37:41.025 --> 37:46.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their troops in rural areas, and
one of them
is a key demand by the FARC:

37:46.865 --> 37:53.705 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOAQUIN GOMEZ (through
translator): That paramilitarism
ends as a state policy. That's
it, that they

37:53.738 --> 37:58.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get rid of it. It's the only
obstacle that
exists, because, while it
exists, it's like

37:58.176 --> 38:02.213 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
walking with one foot in the
grave.

38:02.247 --> 38:07.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Gomez and other
rebels worry
that if the FARC become a purely
political

38:07.318 --> 38:12.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
organization, they will meet the
same fate
as thousands of activists,
social and political

38:12.257 --> 38:15.059 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
leaders who have been
assassinated.

38:15.093 --> 38:19.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If the FARC are to disarm, Gomez
says the
state should stop using its
weapons as a tool

38:19.597 --> 38:21.399 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of political repression.

38:21.432 --> 38:27.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOAQUIN GOMEZ (through
translator): That would
mean that weapons of the state
aren't used

38:27.505 --> 38:31.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in assassinations of political
leaders, trade
unionists, or leftists. And our
weapons would

38:32.010 --> 38:35.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be kept at a distance from us.
We propose
that a third country hold on to
them.

38:35.713 --> 38:39.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: While the presence
of the guerrilla
is feared in various regions,
the vacuum of

38:39.951 --> 38:42.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their absence worries many
locals.

38:42.120 --> 38:45.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LILIANA, Colombia (through
translator): At
the point of signing a peace
agreement, which

38:45.890 --> 38:51.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we support, we will feel very
worried, because,
with living in a conflict zone,
paramilitaries

38:51.062 --> 38:55.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
may come in and disappear us,
one by one,
or kill us, and who will protect
us? With

38:55.900 --> 38:59.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the FARC here, one feels a
security that that
won't happen.

38:59.537 --> 39:04.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOAQUIN GOMEZ (through
translator): What is
being sought is reconciliation.,
not impunity,

39:04.742 --> 39:06.911 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but reconciliation.

39:06.945 --> 39:12.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Commander Joaquin
Gomez faces
narco-trafficking charges in the
U.S. and

39:12.984 --> 39:19.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a $2.5 million reward for his
capture. In
Colombia, he's wanted for the
kidnapping and

39:19.224 --> 39:21.626 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
assassination of a governor.

39:21.659 --> 39:27.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOAQUIN GOMEZ (through
translator): There
has to be a general amnesty,
except for crimes

39:27.332 --> 39:32.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
against humanity. And there has
to be a form
of justice that isn't punitive,
but restorative.

39:32.604 --> 39:37.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: A peace agreement
will call all
parties to the conflict, the
FARC, as much

39:37.809 --> 39:43.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as members of the state and
military, to face
a special justice system that
offers alternative

39:43.314 --> 39:48.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sentences. Most of the FARC's
rank-and-file
will receive amnesties, and for
when they

39:48.586 --> 39:53.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do, some are being trained to
use new tools
for political communication.

39:53.591 --> 39:58.596 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BORIS, FARC (through
translator): We're preparing
ourselves here for political
battle, to get

39:58.630 --> 40:03.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ready for a new environment. We
will pick
up cameras and drop our arms.

40:03.301 --> 40:09.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Welcoming the
prospect of peace,
but wary of the uncertainties to
come.

40:10.008 --> 40:18.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEXANDRA NARINO, FARC (through
translator):
When a peace accord is signed,
that doesn't

40:18.783 --> 40:23.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mean that peace starts. The
silencing of weapons
isn't peace. I think it's
afterwards that

40:23.921 --> 40:32.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the difficult part starts. And
the most interesting
part, the construction of peace
with social

40:32.697 --> 40:35.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
justice, I want to be there.

40:35.600 --> 40:42.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: For tonight, an air
of optimism
and hope takes over, as one step
of many is

40:42.507 --> 40:48.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
taken on the long and difficult
road to peace.

40:48.780 --> 40:55.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
reporting with Bruno
Federico, I'm Nadja Drost in
Putumayo, Colombia.

40:55.186 --> 40:58.022 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Extraordinary
reporting.

40:58.056 --> 41:03.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And later this week, we will
look at how Colombia's
massive cocaine trade could be
affected by

41:03.528 --> 41:08.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a peace agreement.

41:08.499 --> 41:19.977 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Now back to terror
in Turkey.

41:20.011 --> 41:25.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attack on a pedestrian
street in Istanbul
on Sunday, the fourth suicide
bombing in Turkey

41:25.149 --> 41:31.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this year, was, according to
President Erdogan,
one of the biggest and bloodiest
terrorist

41:31.656 --> 41:33.725 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
waves in its history.

41:33.758 --> 41:37.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We take an intimate look now at
the violence,
and how it shapes daily life.

41:37.862 --> 41:43.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Decorated Marine veteran Elliot
Ackerman served
in Iraq and Afghanistan. His
debut novel,

41:43.267 --> 41:49.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Green on Blue," is a war story
told from
the perspective of an Afghan
boy. Ackerman

41:49.273 --> 41:51.843 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
now lives with his family in
Istanbul.

41:51.876 --> 41:55.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELLIOT ACKERMAN, Author, "Green
on Blue":
On an unseasonably warm morning
the past January

41:55.513 --> 42:01.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Istanbul, an Islamic State
suicide bomber
detonated himself in a
Sultanahmet, a central

42:01.085 --> 42:02.887 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sightseeing district.

42:02.920 --> 42:07.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He killed eleven tourists, 10 of
them Germans.
At the moment of the blast, I
was sitting

42:07.725 --> 42:12.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in an outside cafe nearby.
Almost immediately,
my phone lit up with concerned
calls from

42:12.864 --> 42:15.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
friends and family back home in
the U.S.

42:15.833 --> 42:20.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This was the third Islamic State
bombing in
Turkey since June. I had moved
to Istanbul

42:20.705 --> 42:25.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two years before with my family
to work on
a book. But I had also moved
here to give

42:25.243 --> 42:28.513 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
my children the experience of
living abroad.

42:28.546 --> 42:33.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What better place to expand
their world view
than Istanbul? It's a city
defined by its

42:33.151 --> 42:38.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
divisions, by Bosphorus Strait
that splits
Europe from Asia and by its
religious history,

42:38.689 --> 42:41.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
having once been the seat of
power for both
Christian and Islamic empires.

42:41.959 --> 42:46.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of my fondest memories is of
the spring
we moved here. That's when the
tulips are

42:47.031 --> 42:52.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in bloom. They blossom
everywhere, in long
rows along the streets, in
planters tucked

42:52.670 --> 42:56.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into the city squares, even
sprouting up through
the broken sidewalks.

42:56.607 --> 43:03.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I spent those months watching my
children
explore this ancient city among
its new flowers.

43:03.214 --> 43:07.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The night after the bombing, I
went out to
dinner with a few Turkish
friends. Among them

43:07.952 --> 43:12.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a well-known journalist. Weeks
before, the
authorities had imprisoned two
of his colleagues

43:13.024 --> 43:18.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for spying and revealing state
secrets after
they printed a story about
government collusion

43:18.262 --> 43:21.032 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with Islamic fighters inside of
Syria.

43:21.065 --> 43:26.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When the topic of the bombing
came up, he
said that he was far more afraid
of Turkey's

43:26.370 --> 43:31.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more increasingly toxic politics
around the
issue of terrorism than of
terrorism itself.

43:31.509 --> 43:37.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Politics, he said, can be
defined as the acquisition
or maintenance of power. You can
do this in

43:37.248 --> 43:41.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
two ways, by either dividing
people or uniting
them.

43:41.452 --> 43:46.357 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Uniting people is very
difficult, he explained.
But dividing them is far easier.
When I asked

43:46.390 --> 43:51.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
how you divide people, his
answer was a single
word: fear.

43:51.696 --> 43:55.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We then speculated about why the
bombing had
taken place in Sultanahmet,
close to the famous

43:55.900 --> 44:00.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Blue Mosque. The bomber could
have killed
far more people if he had
attacked a subway

44:00.104 --> 44:05.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
station at rush hour or a
shopping mall. Consensus
was that the Islamic State
wanted to harm

44:05.943 --> 44:07.678 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the tourist industry.

44:07.712 --> 44:10.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I remembered all of the
concerned phone
calls I had received from home,
it seemed

44:10.882 --> 44:15.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
likely that fewer and fewer
Westerners would
be planning their vacations to
the city.

44:15.052 --> 44:20.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then the man at the table next
interrupted
us. He owned a hotel in
Sultanahmet, and told

44:20.791 --> 44:25.596 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
us that a wonderful and
surprising thing had
happened after the bombing. In a
small act

44:25.630 --> 44:31.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of defiance and solidarity,
German vacationers
had booked his hotel to
capacity. They had

44:31.068 --> 44:34.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
chosen not to be afraid.

44:34.105 --> 44:38.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Much of current U.S. politics is
defined by
the rhetoric of fear. Whether
the topic is

44:38.809 --> 44:44.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
terrorism, gun control or
immigration, our
fears are manipulated. We are
encouraged to

44:44.448 --> 44:46.284 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be divided.

44:46.317 --> 44:50.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The longer I stay in Istanbul,
the more I
realize that the education I'm
giving my children

44:50.421 --> 44:55.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is not so much as cultural, but
moral. It's
about teaching them to live
without fear.

